<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>2719</anchor> <rss>dannypsnl.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Person</taxon> <addr>dannypsnl</addr>  <route>dannypsnl.xml</route>   <title>Lîm Tsú-thuàn</title> <meta name="external">https://dannypsnl.me/</meta><meta name="position">Compiler Developer</meta><meta name="institution">Second State</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter/> <backmatter><contributions/> <context/> <related/> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>2720</anchor> <rss>2023-10-06.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Entry</taxon> <addr>2023-10-06</addr>  <route>2023-10-06.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>6</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>2023-10-06</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Applied a patch to <link href="jms-005P.xml" type="local" title="Forester">Forester</link> from <link href="dannypsnl.xml" type="local" title="Lîm Tsú-thuàn">Lîm Tsú-thuàn</link> to allow taxa to be overridden during transclusion.</p><p>Meeting of new faculty with head of department <link href="alastairberesford.xml" type="local" title="Alastair Beresford">Alastair Beresford</link>.</p><p>Working on revision of <link href="sterling-2022-existentials.xml" type="local" title="Reflections on existential types">reflections on existential types</link>. I am also thinking about whether it would be worth writing a paper about the tensor products of pointed dcpos in <link href="jms-001E.xml" type="local" title="Constructive domain theory">constructive domain theory</link>. My concern is the constructive cocompleteness of the category of dcpos remains slightly vague — this is claimed in various places, and it is very likely that the results of <link href="jung-moshier-vickers-2008.xml" type="local" title="Presenting dcpos and dcpo algebras">presenting dcpos and dcpo algebras</link> are constructive.</p><p>Apparently I completely forgot about the FICS special issue that I had been planning to submit to with <link href="danielgratzer.xml" type="local" title="Daniel Gratzer">Daniel Gratzer</link> and <link href="larsbirkedal.xml" type="local" title="Lars Birkedal">Lars Birkedal</link>; the <link href="2023-10-02.xml" type="local" title="2023-10-02">deadline</link> has passed and there is some chance of extension, but I don’t think we have anything to send after all.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>2721</anchor> <rss>jms-009Q.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Changelog</taxon> <addr>jms-009Q</addr>  <route>jms-009Q.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>9</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Forester 2.5 [unreleased]</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Thanks to <link href="dannypsnl.xml" type="local" title="Lîm Tsú-thuàn">Lîm Tsú-thuàn</link> and <link href="vikramanchoudhury.xml" type="local" title="Vikraman Choudhury">Vikraman Choudhury</link> for their suggestions and bug reports on the <link href="https://lists.sr.ht/~jonsterling/forester-discuss" type="external">mailing list</link>.</p><ul>  <li>A new <code>\iftex</code> command has been added, following a suggestion of <link href="vikramanchoudhury.xml" type="local" title="Vikraman Choudhury">Vikraman Choudhury</link>; this can be used to control the behavior of macros, depending on whether they are being rendered by <tex>\LaTeX</tex> or by the browser. For example, <code>\iftex{foo}{bar}</code> will become <code>foo</code> when passed to the <tex>\LaTeX</tex> tool, but will be reated as <code>bar</code> when rendering for the browser.</li>  <li>A new <link href="jms-005O.xml" type="local" title="Forester 2.1">fluid binding</link> <code>\transclude/taxon</code> has been added to the <link href="jms-0067.xml" type="local" title="Flexible transclusion options in Forester 2.2">transclusion overrides</link>, which can be used to locally change the taxon of a transcluded tree. Thanks to <link href="dannypsnl.xml" type="local" title="Lîm Tsú-thuàn">Lîm Tsú-thuàn</link> for implementing this.</li></ul></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>2722</anchor> <rss>2023-09-23.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Entry</taxon> <addr>2023-09-23</addr>  <route>2023-09-23.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>9</month> <day>23</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>2023-09-23</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p><link href="jms-007M.xml" type="local" title="Forester 2.4">Forester 2.4</link> is now released on opam. <link href="dannypsnl.xml" type="local" title="Lîm Tsú-thuàn">Lîm Tsú-thuàn</link> is interested in implementing a <code>forester watch</code> command, as we have discussed on the mailing list.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>2723</anchor> <rss>jms-009H.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>jms-009H</addr>  <route>jms-009H.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>9</month> <day>22</day></date>  <title>List of <link href="tfmt-000R.xml" type="local" title="Forests and trees of evergreen notes">forests</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><ul>  <li><link href="dannypsnl.xml" type="local" title="Lîm Tsú-thuàn">Lîm Tsú-thuàn</link>: <link href="https://dannypsnl.me/index.xml" type="external">dannypsnl.me</link></li>  <li><link href="masanoriogino.xml" type="local" title="Masanori Ogino">Masanori Ogino</link>: <link href="https://trail.brackets-salad.com/index.xml" type="external">trail.brackets-salad.com</link></li>  <li><link href="yueniu.xml" type="local" title="Yue Niu">Yue Niu</link>: 